content.detailedDescription: I was out for a late evening walk by a local canal bank when i noticed, in my peripheral vision, two auburn colored lights rising from a tree line in the distance. at first i thought they may have been helicopters, since they were coming from the ‘somewhat’ general direction of a shuttered airbase (castle afb); but, being i’ve lived in the vicinity for over 40 years, and have seen many types of aircraft come and go, these looked like nothing i’d seen before; so, i stopped and took a photo of both orbs. as i was doing so, more started to ascend from the same general area, so i quickly switched my phone to ‘video’, and started to video them. those were the first two of approximately 15 of those auburn colored orbs i witnessed that night in merced county. they came up from the north, low, over the horizon, slow and steady, apparently noiseless, in an unorganized assent and headed southeast, crossing over state highway 99. and, though i could hear the relatively steady noise of the not too distant traffic, i did not hear any distinct prop or jet noise from them  through the whole 15 minute duration of the event, as they rose above the tree line and faded into the distance before blinking out. also, anything with a prop, at the distance they were in comparison to the traffic, i would have definitely been able to hear. in fact, you would think a group of anything that large would make some sort of racket; as they weren't that distant from me and didn't reach that high an altitude before blinking out. also, aside from the solid orangish light they emanated, they didn't have any wing or tail navigation, proximity or flashing-position lamps from what i could see. neither from their front as they approached nor from the rear as they departed. note: this happened in merced so i was hoping anyone from the area traveling on the north or south lanes of highway 99, at approximately 9:00pm to 9:15pm, just over the 16th street overpass may have also seen them, as (from my point of view) they looked as though they may have crossed that highway.
content.summary: Noticed auburn colored orbs ascending from a distant tree line, 5 to 6 seconds apart, then more from the same, general area.

content.detailedDescription:
A friend & i were working the overnight shift & had just stepped into the lot behind the building for some air. my friend first noticed the object, & pointed it out to me. she asked me if i thought it was a star, because it was unusually large & bright. when i saw it, i knew it could not be a star.
the light was brilliant, & it was constantly changing its intensity. it melted into red, pink, orange, white, yellow & (occasionally) a green-blue at random & with no apparent pattern or timing. we thought it could be a satellite, but it moved like a mosquito, hovering all around & up & down. at this time the object was far above & away from us to the north.
after a few minutes, my friend jokingly called out to it, asking it to come closer. we were just chatting & watching it, when suddenly it began to zigzag upwards above the tallest pine trees, putting it into very clear view. that was when we could see that the light was actually coming from the base of a larger, round, black object.
as we stood there & watched, it moved slowly closer to us. after a few minutes of this we got scared & ran inside. about ten minutes later, though, curiosity got the best of us & we went back out.
this time the light was to our right, floating high above the neighboring building. we attempted to record it on our phones, but it was not visible over the glare on the cameras from the street lights. we watched & discussed what we were seeing: a rounded, flat disc with a rounded/square top that was only visible sometimes; it was very large and solid. we started to get scared again, but we continued to stand & stare. after a few more minutes passed by, a second light emerged from the bottom of the hat, & dropped about a hundred feet. it hovered there, & then went back and merged with the original light. it was about this time that we were startled by approximately three unexplained flashes of white light that illuminated everything all around us. a few minutes after that, the colorful light in the sky blinked out, & the object was gone. almost in the same moment, we heard a strange machine-like noise that sounded unlike anything we'd ever heard. it was very loud, & we ran inside the building & didn't even want to talk about what we had just witnessed for quite awhile. it gave me the worst migraine i've ever had, which lasted for about twelve hours.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
content.summary: A hat shaped object with bright lights was floating erratically in the sky - a light emerged at the base & then returned, & then there were flashes all around us. after thirty minutes, it disappeared & a bizarre machine noise came from seemingly no where.

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were hanging out at the beach when i noticed a fast spherical object going east at a high rate of speed them decelerating to an almost stationary speed. when i pointed out to my wife, she stated " why are you talking about, i don't see a damn thing" i took off my expensive polarized fishing sun glasses and i could no longer see the object until i put my glasses back on. i then have my glasses to my wife who was very skeptical at first, as soon as she put my glasses on she saw the object too. the object was changing its speeds from fast to slow, to almost hovering before it started to ascend well above plane altitude. there was a plane in the far distance way further out then the sphere object and you could visible see the difference between the plane and sphere objects shape. the object ascended well above any plane and stopped on a dime and hovered for a couple seconds before it just vanished. the day itself was a very warm day with no cloud coverage around and about five minutes after the object dispersed a jet going high speeds went slashing by the area the object had been. i'm not completely sure how far the object was out over the ocean, so size is very hard to determine, but i would guess it would have to be over 20 feet in size to visible from that distance. i hope others report this, but i do know that the object was not visible with the naked eye nor another type of high end sun glasses like my wife was wearing.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path then hovering
content.summary: Spherical object that was unable to see with naked eye, i could only see with my polerized fishing glasses

content.detailedDescription: I do believe that it was mid summer 06 or 07. i was riding my bike down lakeshore dr. heading north out of ludington, mi.  to my parents house witch is about 5-6 miles out of town. it was around midnight and ive made this trip excessively around that time in my life. there are few lights down that stretch of road. i left a friends house between 11:30 and midnight to go home, which is usually between a 20 min-40 min bike ride depending on how i was feeling. i made it a little over half way that night and was coming up to the last street light in that area before turning on to another road. as i was riding in the darkness toward the light i felt a sudden skip in my sight and did not feel right, disoriented. i stopped and stepped off my bike to collect myself. it seemed like i glitched up the road 10 or 15 feet. i got on my bike after that and continued to ride home not really thinking much about the situation until i got home and looked at a clock. i started to panic a little because it was just after 5 am. like i said the trip only takes 40 min max. around 5 hours were gone and the only logical answer was this skip. i believe in e.T. and this event just blew my mind because of the fact that if i was abducted, they seemed to pick me up and put me back all in motion on my pedal bike. ive never came across any kind of this information doing research. over the next year id say there were 2 other skips either walking or riding in that same area. they were not as noticeable as the first one or what i assume was the first. the second one i barely noticed and i'm not sure the time i left town, but i think there was an half hour to an hour missing. the third time i felt it wasnt even noticable. i just felt the same feeling and assuming. ive had a few significant paranormal events around that time in my life and the greatest one was on the same stretch of road. this is making me question the case of abduction. thats a different story. id like some feed back on this and see what the experts think. id like to say that i'm a very logical person and these event make me uneasy even today. thank u for your time reading this.

the attached image looks very similar to the streak that i observed

content.detailedDescription:
I was riding my bike back home going down the road between hull's trail and the buildings on langford parkway. i stopped behind the bc hydro building when i felt as though i should look up.

this is when i noticed a small black triangle with rounded corners hovering directly over me, underneath the cloud cover. it looked like it was 1mm wide with how high it was. it wobbled and spun as it hovered in place.

i kept watching it as i moved my bike forward, it followed me, moving slowly. i stopped my bike again and stood watching it hover above me for about 5 minutes. at this point it slowly started to move northward from its position above me. i took out my phone, intending to take a photo, keeping my eye on it. as i brought my phone up, it ascended into the clouds out of view, evading the camera.

the whole event lasted between 11:55am to 12:00pm pacific standard time.
content.summary: Wobbling and rotating black triangle hovering overhead behind quality foods, followed me before disappearing

content.summary: Bright yellow-orange triangle hovering at treetop level about a mile away from the bonaparte bridge

content.detailedDescription:

2.  my wife looked out the window and saw an object with bright light high in the sky.

3.  we thought the object could be a sophisticate, large drone, possibly military.  however when we reviewed the video at the end frame by frame it appears to spin and then disappear.

4.  the object hovered stationary for several minutes.  using my hd video camera zoomed in at 60x i could see an a fram shape for each structure, a red and green light in the middle, and 3 bright white lights on top.  it began spinning and then disappeared as shown frame by frame on the video.  it returned a few minutes later in the same location but facing a different direction.  it hovered stationary again and then disappeared.  the video zoom did not resolve well but the object appeared to change color all at once to red before it disappeared.

5.  we were excited to see the object even if it turns out to be just a drone.  my wife posted the video clip to her facebook account and friends were shocked.  some said it was just a drone, but other did not.

6.  we lost sight of the object because it disappeared.  please see the video clip as it is all there.  i have 4 videos total but have processed only 1 to remove the audio and clip just the best section to reduce file size.  the sequence of the video is continuous and has not been modified.

please contact me if you think this is a ufo or just a drone.

when it appeared in the sky i was at the balcony of a house and locals there showed it to me at 8:08 pm. they told me that these kind of objects were appearing there regularly. i there for holiday thus i had no idea about that. firstly i thought it was a plane but it kept on appearing at the next days and i took my camera and took some photos. it really appered regularly between 8 pm and 8:30 pm.

best regards

michael n
